      "comment": "EYESEALITTLE (7) resumes after finishing sixth at her latest appearance at Bendigo on November 26. Talented and has plenty of upside. Interesting to see what unfolds from this wide draw. This doesn't look as hard so she is set to play a significant role. HAPPILY (8) good effort to finish second two starts ago at Hamilton but didn't measure up at her latest appearance over 2240m at Melton, beaten 55 metres into 12th after being up on the pace. Can settle just behind them and wait on the sprint lane. Has the ability to take care of this field. SEASIDE SHOW (9) is the next elect off a last-start win by 14 metres at Mildura over 1790m. MISSMALACHITE (2) has drawn to advantage and should give backers a great sight.",
